byline.original: By ABBY GOODNOUGH and REED ABELSON

abstract: Stories of some of beneficiaries of Affordable Care Act offer insight into strengths and weaknesses of program; while many of most vulnerable Americans have secured health insurance under law, subsidies it provides and penalties it levies have discouraged young and healthy people from  participating in health insurance marketplaces; as result, some insurers are spending more on claims than they collect in premiums.

lead_paragraph: The Affordable Care Act has not enticed enough young, healthy people into the insurance markets it created, so the people who benefit most from it also burden it.
